author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump told reporters he could potentially invoke the Insurrection Act, a law that allows the deployment of troops in the US in certain limited situations, as civilians continue to protest against immigration raids in cities such as Portland, Chicago and Los Angeles.
title: What is the Insurrection Act?

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kasie Hunt sits down with Oregon Governor Tina Kotek to discuss her state's challenge to President Trump's effort to deploy the National Guard to Portland, as well as her discussion with DHS Secretary Kristi Noem. #CNN #News
title: Oregon Governor on her meeting with DHS Secretary Kristi Noem

author: CNN
description: Soybeans are America's largest agricultural export, and about half of the $24 billion crop went to China. This year, that market is effectively zero after China imposed 20% tariffs on US soybeans in retaliation for tariffs on Chinese goods. CNN's Erica Hill speaks with soybean farmer Scott Brown about his situation. #CNN #News
title: Soybean farmer on Trump's tariff war: 'I mean, where do they want me to market this stuff?'

author: CNN
description: Texas National Guard troops have arrived at the Elwood Army Reserve Center outside Chicago. CNN's Omar Jimenez reports.
title: Texas National Guard seen outside of Chicago

author: CNN
description: Keith Siegel and his wife, Aviva, were kidnapped by Hamas terrorists on October 7, 2023. Keith was held in captivity for 484 days. He joined Dana Bash two years after that brutal attack with an urgent plea on behalf of his fellow hostages, "As moral human beings, it's all of our responsibility to do whatever we can to bring them all back as soon as possible." #CNN #News
title: Former hostage: brutality, violence, and cruelty of Hamas terrorists 'still haunt me'

author: CNN
description:
Typhoon Matmo brought relentless rain that sent floodwater pouring into a hospital in Moc Chau, burst a dam in Lang Son and turned Hanoi streets into lakes. It's the second major flood disaster to hit Vietnam in the last week.
#cnn #news
title: Typhoon Matmo unleashes devastating flooding in Vietnam

description: Sen. Bernie Sanders speaks with Kaitlan Collins on "The Source." #CNN #News
title: Sen. Bernie Sanders (I-VT) on government shutdown

title: Bondi gets upset about senator's merger question

author: CNN
description:
Members of the Texas National Guard have now arrived near Chicago after being mobilized by President Donald Trump, a law enforcement source familiar with the deployment tells CNN. 

Approximately 200 troops were part of the initial deployment and more Texas soldiers could be brought in soon, the source said.  #CNN #News
title: Texas National Guard members arrive near Chicago

author: CNN
description:
Attorney General Pam Bondi testified for a contentious 4 and a half hours before the Senate Judiciary Committee on Tuesday. Bondi continuously deflected questions from Democrats on controversial issues, including the Jeffery Epstein files, prosecution of former FBI Director James Comey and legal rationale for using the national guard in US cities.

CNN legal analyst Elliot Williams reacts to the testimony, and Manu Raju discusses with his "Inside Politics" panel: CNN senior White House correspondent Kristen Holmes, NPR's Ayesha Rascoe, and CNN senior reporter Edward-Isaac Dovere. #CNN #News
title: Senators grill Attorney General Bondi in tense hearing

author: CNN
description: President Trump refused to commit to offering all federal workers back pay once the government shutdown ends. #cnn #trump #shutdown #workers #backpay
title: Trump says some federal workers don't deserve back pay

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Shimon Prokupecz speaks with residents in Portland, Oregon, some of whom tell him they don’t view their city as “war-ravaged” as President Donald Trump put it in a Truth Social post. #cnn #news
title: Trump says Portland is ‘war-ravaged.’ Hear what residents say

author: CNN
description: As the government shutdown continues, President Donald Trump said “it depends who we’re talking about” when asked if furloughed federal workers will get back pay after it ends. CNN’s Alayna Treene reports. #CNN #News
title: Trump doesn't commit to paying all furloughed federal workers

author: CNN
description: Two years after their daughters were killed on October 7 Sigal and Menashe Mansuri are fighting for answers and accountability, demanding the Israeli government establish a state commission of inquiry to investigate the failures that led to the attack. CNN’s Jeremy Diamond reports. #cnn #news
title: Israelis still fighting for investigation into Oct 7

description:
During an oversight hearing, Attorney General Pam Bondi got visibly angry with Sen. Richard Blumenthal (D-CT) after he asked her about any conversations she had about a merger lawsuit.

#CNN #News #PamBondi #Politics
title: Bondi gets upset about senator's merger question

author: CNN
description:
Israelis are today commemorating two years since Hamas’ October 7 attacks on their country. Around 1,200 people were killed in the attacks, with 250 others taken hostage, sparking the ensuing war in Gaza that has killed more than 67,000 Palestinians.

0:00 CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with Ruby Chen, father of Itay Chen, the youngest Israeli-American hostage taken on October 7
6:35 CNN's Audie Cornish reports on the Gaza ceasefire talks and speaks with Alon Pinkas, former Israeli consul general for New York
12:46 CNN Jerusalem correspondent Jeremy Diamond reports on the fights defining Israeli society
19:54 CNN's Becky Anderson reports on the Israeli commemorations of October 7 and the new Israeli attacks reported in Gaza
21:08 CNN Jerusalem bureau chief Oren Liebermann speaks with Israeli opposition leader Yair Lapid
22:43 CNN international diplomatic editor Nic Robertson reports on the Gaza ceasefire talks underway in Cairo #CNN #News
title: As Israel marks two years since the October 7 attacks, Gaza ceasefire talks underway

author: CNN
description: French President Emmanuel Macron was seen taking a walk along the river Seine, shortly after the resignation of yet another prime minister, which plunged the country further into political crisis. CNN’s Melissa Bell takes a look at the potential options the French leader faces. #CNN #News
title: What are Macron’s options?

author: CNN
description:
Sen. Dick Durbin (D-IL) and Attorney General Pam Bondi clashed over the Trump administration sending National Guard troops into Illinois. Bondi refused to answer Durbin's questions about the legal rationale.

#CNN #News #Chicago #NationalGuard #PamBondi
title: Bondi pressed on National Guard deployment to Chicago

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration has produced a classified legal opinion that justifies lethal strikes against a secret and expansive list of cartels and suspected drug traffickers, according to multiple people familiar with the matter. CNN’s Zachary Cohen reports.  #CNN #News
title: Exclusive: Classified DOJ opinion authorizes strikes on secret list of cartels, sources say

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jeremy Diamond spent a recent Saturday night with Vicki Cohen, a mother at the forefront of the hostage families' movement in Israel. Two years after her son, an Israeli soldier, was taken captive by Hamas, Vicki remains hopeful for a peace deal that would bring the hostages home despite losing faith in her government. #cnn #israel #hamas #gaza
title: Israeli mother still fighting for her captive son

author: CNN
description: Eighty years after the Japanese surrendered, formally ending World War II, CNN’s Stephanie Elam sat down with US Navy veteran Robert Somrak, who served on the USS Missouri during the war. Somrak says he joined the Navy because he loved the sea, the water and he knew in the Navy he’d have “a clean bed and good food.” He recalls what life was like on the “Mighty Mo,” witnessing the aftermath of a kamikaze attack and watching as members of the Japanese Imperial Government boarded the Missouri on September 2, 1945, to take part in the surrender ceremony.  #CNN #News
title: WWII Navy veteran describes household item he made from piece of a Kamikaze plane

author: CNN
description:
Science educator and CEO of The Planetary Society Bill Nye is, along with more than 300 other science advocates, urging Congress to save NASA from the Trump administration's proposed 47% funding cut.

Bill Nye joins Kaitlan Collins on "The Source." #CNN #News
title: Nye: 'The founders put the word 'science' in the US Constitution. That is a remarkable thing'

author: CNN
description: Despite a missile threat and a power outage in Belgorod - just north of Russia’s border with Ukraine - a concert at the Philharmonic went on uninterrupted. Audience members lit up the stage with flashlights, helping the musicians continue to perform. #cnn #news
title: Musicians play on amid wartime air raid sirens

author: CNN
description: In an interview with Jimmy Fallon, Taylor Swift explained why she is not performing at the Super Bowl halftime show.
title: Why Taylor Swift isn't performing at the Super Bowl

author: CNN
description: Donald Trump's approval rating essentially hasn't changed in the past year, and a majority of Americans believe he's doing what he promised when running in 2024. CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten runs the polling numbers. #CNN #News
title: Is Trump who voters thought he was? CNN's Harry Enten runs the numbers

author: CNN
description: The ongoing government shutdown is having an impact on travelers across the US as air traffic controller staffing issues have led to delays at major airports and forced pilots in some areas to pivot to alternative workflows.  #CNN #News
title: Government shutdown causes air travel delays across the country

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump suggested he might invoke the Insurrection Act to send federal troops to cities like Portland and Chicago. The centuries-old law, first passed in 1792 and last updated in 1871, allows the president to deploy military forces domestically in limited circumstances, even without a state’s consent.  #CNN #News
title: Trump floats using the Insurrection Act to deploy National Guard troops to US cities

author: CNN
description: Chicago Mayor Brandon Johnson says he's creating "ICE-free zones." White House Deputy Chief of Staff Stephen Miller speculates that Black people in Chicago are delighted that immigration laws are being enforced since undocumented immigrants "are stealing their housing, jobs, and resources." #CNN #News
title: Toobin: I doubt Stephen Miller knows what Black people in Chicago are thinking

author: CNN
description: Passengers at Burbank airport faced delays of more than two hours on Monday evening as the control tower was empty due to staff shortages. Air traffic controllers are considered essential workers, so they have to work during a government shutdown but are not paid. Twelve Federal Aviation Administration facilities saw staffing shortages Monday night. #cnn #burbank #shutdown
title: Burbank airport tower unmanned for hours

author: CNN
description:
Tech platforms are increasingly trying to figure out how old you are. Why is this happening? CT Jones, a culture writer at Rolling Stone, has been reporting on the rollout of new age verification laws. They explain how these laws work and what they mean for anyone navigating the internet.

Listen to the full episode of CNN’s Terms of Service podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tosyt100725

#cnn #news #technology #tech #websafety #journalism #techjournalism
title: Why tech platforms are now asking for your age | Terms of Service

author: CNN
description: Three people who were on board a medical helicopter are in critical condition after it crashed on a Sacramento highway Monday evening, according to fire officials. #CNN #news
title: Medical helicopter crashes on Sacramento highway

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins speaks with Bill Nye, "The Science Guy," about the potential impact of proposed massive cuts to NASA's budget.
title: Bill Nye sounds alarm on Trump plan to cut NASA funding

author: CNN
description: Activists onboard the Global Sumud Flotilla have described being denied food, clean water and access to legal advice while being detained in Israel. Those released also said they were forced to watch images of the October 7 Hamas attack on Israel, and some allege that beatings and violence were common. Israel’s Foreign Ministry has called the claims ‘brazen lies’ and maintains that it upheld all legal rights of the detainees.
title: Flotilla activists describe brutal treatment in Israel

author: CNN
description: Famed primatologist Jane Goodall gave an interview on Netflix's show “Famous Last Words” that would only be released after her death. Goodall shared some candid words about world leaders.
title: Netflix show reveals Jane Goodall's 'Famous Last Words'

author: CNN
description: Taylor Swift’s “The Life of a Showgirl” has uncharacteristically faced mixed reviews since its release last week. CNN's Lisa France has the details.
title: ‘The Life of a Showgirl’ divides Swift fans
